{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-Mortem Nudge on Artifact Tasks",
  "description": "When Richard moves an Asana task tagged 'Artifact' from Ready to In Progress, if the task description doesn't contain a pre-mortem passing the specificity bar (named person OR named mechanism in the 'because' clause), surface a nudge asking him to write one. Non-blocking \u2014 Richard can proceed without the pre-mortem, but the hook logs the override so we can see if the nudge is being ignored too often and upgrade to a hard block.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "1. Fetch the task description via TaskeiGetTask or Asana MCP. If the pre-mortem is missing or fails the specificity bar, reply with a clear nudge\n2. If the pre-mortem passes, confirm briefly and let the state change complete silently.\n3. Log the outcome to context/active/pre-mortem-log.jsonl with fields: {task_gid, timestamp, had_pre_mortem (bool), passed_bar (bool), override, pre_mortem_text}.\nRichard is about to start work on a task tagged 'Artifact'. Before he begins, check whether the task description contains a pre-mortem passing this specificity bar: **Pre-mortem template (5 lines):**\n\"Six weeks from now, this artifact didn't land. Why?\" **Specificity bar:** the 'because' clause must end with EITHER a named person (Brandon, Kate, Todd, Andrew, Lena, Lorena, Alexis, Carlos, or another named individual from memory.md) OR a named mechanism (data pipeline, refresh cadence, publish workflow, handoff, review gate, writing voice, attribution model, dashboard, Brazil build, Asana write, Slack channel, or similar specific system/process). **Fail examples**:\n- \"It wasn't good enough\"\n- \"We ran out of time\"\n- \"Didn't have the right data\"\n- \"Unclear scope\" **Pass examples** (accept):\n- \"Kate will push back because the data doesn't connect to a decision she owns\"\n- \"The data pipeline won't have caught up to W20 actuals by the time Brandon reviews, so the numbers will shift mid-review\"\n- \"Lena will override the phased approach mid-project because she did the same on Q1 AU\" **Action:** Keep the nudge short \u2014 6-8 lines max. Richard is in flow; the point is to protect the flow, not break it. If the log accumulates high override rates, surface this to Richard in the weekly retrospective so we know the nudge is ignored and may need to upgrade to a block. Soul.md principle #5 invisible-over-visible applies"
  }
}